{"name":"Red-Hood Iskra","type":"npc","flags":{"btActorType":"broken_one","btNpcSubtype":"main","btCustomOL":"5"},"img":"icons/svg/blood.svg","system":{"npcType":"broken_one","attributes":{"soma":{"max":0,"current":0},"wounds":{"max":4,"current":0,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}},"xp":0},"descriptors":["I possess the strength and agility of a wolf. I hide my face with a rudimentary wooden mask that I made with my own hands. I wear a threadbare red cape, the last gift of my mother."],"agenda":"To unleash her animalistic fury on Elizaveta and anyone who defends her. Taking revenge on my mother has become an obsession for me.","gifts":["Wolf's Blood: Iskra is moved by animalistic fury that allows her to act twice in the course of an exchange.","The Senses of a Wolf: Iskra's sense of smell has become infallible. The little girl will always be able to identify someone if she knows their scent, ignoring all kinds of disguise and even magic."],"conditions":[],"notes":""},"_id":"2e86cc08bf1c7189"}
{"_id":"BloodDrawings","name":"Blood Drawings in the Den","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-torn-brown-red.webp","system":{"description":"Crude drawings on the cave walls of the wolves' den, depicting a mother and daughter holding hands. They are drawn in blood, a haunting testament to Iskra's lost innocence and her desperate longing for the maternal love she was denied. These drawings reveal the tragic humanity still present within the wolf-girl.","type":"clue","uses":{"value":0,"max":1},"isImprovement":false,"isDarkEgo":false},"flags":{"scenarioId":"red-hood-iskra","location":"Wolves' Lair - Iskra's personal den","importance":"emotional-clue"}}
{"_id":"BonesPile","name":"Pile of Bones and Corpses","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/commodities/bones/bones-skull-white.webp","system":{"description":"A large cave in the wolves' lair filled with bones and human corpses - the grim remains of the pack's victims. The sight is disturbing and serves as evidence of the wolves' brutality and the danger they pose to Durfort's inhabitants.","type":"clue","uses":{"value":0,"max":1},"isImprovement":false,"isDarkEgo":false},"flags":{"scenarioId":"red-hood-iskra","location":"Wolves' Lair - Large cave chamber","importance":"atmospheric"}}
{"_id":"GerardsLetter","name":"Gerard's Letter to the Papacy","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/sundries/scrolls/scroll-worn-tan-brown.webp","system":{"description":"A letter written in Lord Gerard Dubois' trembling hand, sent to the Papacy begging for help. The letter reads: 'The beasts that menace the Gévaudan are unnatural, fashioned by something other than God.' This desperate plea brought the Order's Hunters to Durfort.","type":"item","uses":{"value":0,"max":1},"isImprovement":false,"isDarkEgo":false},"flags":{"scenarioId":"red-hood-iskra","location":"Dubois Palace","importance":"story-hook"}}
{"_id":"IskrasPendant","name":"Iskra's Pendant","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/sundries/jewelry/necklace-pendant-moon-silver.webp","system":{"description":"An old earthenware pendant that Iskra once made for her mother as a gift, a memento of a rare moment of happiness. Elizaveta tried to dispose of it by throwing it into the old well at the cemetery, but it can still be found at the bottom of the well. This handmade pendant is crude but touching, showing the innocent love of a child for her mother.","type":"item","uses":{"value":0,"max":1},"isImprovement":false,"isDarkEgo":false},"flags":{"scenarioId":"red-hood-iskra","location":"Old Cemetery - Bottom of the well","importance":"crucial-clue"}}
{"_id":"IskrasRedCape","name":"Iskra's Red Cape","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/equipment/back/cloak-layered-red.webp","system":{"description":"A threadbare red cape, the last gift from Iskra's mother before she sent her daughter to her supposed death in the forest. Despite its worn condition, Iskra still wears it as both a memory and a symbol of her quest for revenge. The cape is stained with mud and blood from her time living as a wolf.","type":"item","uses":{"value":0,"max":1},"isImprovement":false,"isDarkEgo":false},"flags":{"scenarioId":"red-hood-iskra","location":"Worn by Iskra","importance":"iconic-item"}}
{"_id":"IskrasWolfMask","name":"Iskra's Wolf Mask","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/equipment/head/mask-carved-wood-tan.webp","system":{"description":"A rudimentary wooden mask carved by Iskra's own hands to hide her face. The mask depicts a wolf's features and serves both to conceal her identity and to express her adopted nature as part of Greskar's wolf pack. The craftsmanship is crude but effective, showing her adaptation to survival in the wild.","type":"item","uses":{"value":0,"max":1},"isImprovement":false,"isDarkEgo":false},"flags":{"scenarioId":"red-hood-iskra","location":"Worn by Iskra","importance":"iconic-item"}}
{"_id":"PatrickDuboisPainting","name":"Portrait of Patrick Dubois","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/sundries/misc/portrait-painting-frame.webp","system":{"description":"An enormous painting of Patrick Dubois, Gerard's late father, hanging in the ceremonial hall. The portrait shows a stern and sullen-looking man who seems to judge his son's incompetence from beyond the grave with ill-concealed contempt. Every room in the palace is filled with flattering paintings of Patrick, a constant reminder of Gerard's inadequacy.","type":"item","uses":{"value":0,"max":1},"isImprovement":false,"isDarkEgo":false},"flags":{"scenarioId":"red-hood-iskra","location":"Dubois Palace - Ceremonial Hall","importance":"atmospheric"}}
{"_id":"PoisonVial","name":"Elizaveta's Poison","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/consumables/potions/potion-bottle-corked-purple.webp","system":{"description":"A powerful poison that Elizaveta keeps hidden in the palace. If Iskra is captured, Elizaveta will attempt to use this poison to eliminate her unwanted daughter once and for all. The poison is potent enough to kill even someone with supernatural resilience.","type":"item","uses":{"value":1,"max":1},"isImprovement":false,"isDarkEgo":false},"flags":{"scenarioId":"red-hood-iskra","location":"Dubois Palace - Elizaveta's possession","importance":"threat"}}
{"_id":"SecretPassageway","name":"Secret Passageway Map","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/sundries/documents/blueprint-axe.webp","system":{"description":"Knowledge of a secret passageway that connects the large dining room to the inner courtyard of the Dubois Palace. This hidden route was used by Iskra and the wolf pack to launch their surprise attack on the mansion. The passageway may also connect to the underground tunnel leading from the wolves' den to the old well in Durfort's main square.","type":"clue","uses":{"value":0,"max":1},"isImprovement":false,"isDarkEgo":false},"flags":{"scenarioId":"red-hood-iskra","location":"Dubois Palace / Wolves' Lair","importance":"tactical-information"}}
{"_id":"WolfTracks","name":"Wolf Tracks and Child's Footprints","type":"descriptor","img":"icons/sundries/misc/paw-print.webp","system":{"description":"In the old cemetery, there are many wolf tracks scattered throughout the grounds. Hidden among them are the prints of two small bare feet, almost certainly belonging to a little girl. These tracks lead deep into the Gévaudan forest, toward the wolves' den. This evidence suggests that a child is somehow involved with the wolf pack.","type":"clue","uses":{"value":0,"max":1},"isImprovement":false,"isDarkEgo":false},"flags":{"scenarioId":"red-hood-iskra","location":"Old Cemetery","importance":"tracking-clue"}}
{"name":"Iskra the Young Wolf","type":"npc","npcType":"broken_one","system":{"attributes":{"soma":{"max":6,"current":6},"wounds":{"max":3,"current":0,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}},"xp":0},"background":"I was abandoned by my mother in a large forest and survived by joining a pack of werewolves. After a year of honing my predatory skills, I tracked down the woman I once called 'Mother' and sank my fangs into her throat. My pack was dismantled by a group of Hunters and the Order captured me. After another year of education and training, I finally found in the Order my new pack and made the Hunters my trusted hunting companions. I serve the Order with strength and dedication, happy to do everything the alpha Hunter asks of me.","equipment":"A red cape of fine workmanship embroidered with the coat of arms of the Order, a wolf mask carved in wood, a broken clay doll (a memento of one of my few happy memories of my mother), a fang from the leader of my old pack, and a rag doll depicting a well-dressed girl — a gift from my beloved grandmother.","descriptors":["When I am calm, I still look like a small and helpless child and, thanks to this, adults tend to underestimate me. I struggle to behave like a normal child, but I can’t keep my wolfish side leashed forever.","I perform my best when I’m cooperating with my hunting companions. I quickly learn the strengths and weaknesses of the pack. I follow every order of anyone I consider more important than me within the pack, without hesitation or remorse.","I am a wolf child and I defend myself with fangs and claws. My sense of smell is infallible. I’m young and I know little about the world, so I am easily intimidated when I face something I don’t know."],"gifts":["The Red Hood: You can spend 1 Soma to look exactly like a common child. Create a Descriptor that contains one of the words Pretty, Small, or Sweet. As long as you maintain your disguise, no adult will notice you or consider you a potential danger. Receive 2 Additional Successes to the first action you take when you decide to drop your disguise and reveal who you are.","Pack: When you coordinate and act with one or more of your teammates against a common threat, you both get 1 Additional Success for your Position Check. At the end of the Scene, if you have resolved a significant issue thanks to the collaboration with your companions, you recover 1 Soma.","Dark Ego - The Young Wolf: Unleash your feral side, ready to bite anyone who opposes your pack. If you get an Outcome with an Increment on a Position Check, you can spend the Increment to take an additional action immediately. You can also inflict 1 Wound on yourself to perform an additional action after your normal action. You can’t perform more than 3 actions per Exchange. You may spend 1 Soma to memorize the smell of a person you are interacting with. You will always recognize them and it will be easy for you to follow their tracks even after a long time."],"darkEgo":{"trigger":"Give free rein to your feral side or fulfill a task for your pack with your wolf skills.","gift":"Dark Ego - The Young Wolf"},"conditions":[],"notes":""},"_id":"a0d0d756222f5918"}
{"name":"Anastazia the Sorrowful Spirit","type":"npc","img":"icons/svg/ghost.svg","flags":{},"token":{"name":"Anastazia the Sorrowful Spirit","img":"icons/svg/ghost.svg"},"system":{"npcType":"broken_one","oppositionLevel":7,"wounds":{"max":3,"current":3,"extra":0},"soma":{"max":0,"current":0},"xp":0,"background":"Anastazia is a restless spirit, bound to the memory of her granddaughter Iskra. She can no longer speak directly to the living, only through dreams, whispers, and visions.","descriptors":["I am a restless spirit, bound to the memory of my granddaughter. My condition as a spirit does not allow me to communicate with the living except through dreams, whispers, and visions."],"gifts":["Spirit: Anastazia is a spirit and can only be damaged by magic. She may appear in a dream to a target, who may resist with a Defense Check or accept contact voluntarily. The target suffers 1 Wound from stress but will receive from Anastazia a vision of a present or past event with a barely whispered phrase.","Loving Grandmother: Anastazia always follows Iskra and protects her from danger. Thanks to her strong will, she can interact with the material world by moving objects and manipulating the environment, even inflicting a Wound on a target. If a subject is likely to help save her granddaughter, Anastazia will simply fill their mind with memories of her."],"agenda":"Preventing further harm to Iskra and finding a way to save my granddaughter’s soul.","conditions":[],"notes":"Anastazia is incorporeal. The Storyteller may allow her to manifest for narrative effect."},"_id":"fdc6b5347bc63c3b"}
